HEADWORD: airbrake
<hw>airbrake</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>a small
parachute or articulated flap to reduce the speed of an
aircraft.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dive brake</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a vehicular brake that operates by compressed air;
especially for heavy vehicles. Same as <er>air brake</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> air brake</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an atomizer to spray by means of
compressed air.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>air brush</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>airbrush</ent>⟦br⟧
